  "text": "Identified three main mechanism categories: (1) ConvergenceWarning is defined in sklearn/exceptions.py and raised via warnings.warn() in ~25 non-test estimator files across linear_model, cluster, decomposition, mixture, neural_network, etc. (2) check_is_fitted is defined in sklearn/utils/validation.py and used across 50+ estimator files to guard predict/transform methods against unfitted estimators, raising NotFittedError (also in exceptions.py). (3) Verbose parameter logging is implemented via self.verbose checks in ~25 estimator files, with shared utilities in sklearn/utils/_user_interface.py (_message_with_time, _print_elapsed_time) and specialized verbose methods in sklearn/mixture/_base.py. The sklearn/base.py file provides the base estimator framework. Files span clustering, decomposition, linear models, neural networks, mixture models, SVMs, ensemble methods, and model selection.",
